- `[P1]` [CanvasPage.tsx](C:\Users\sahil\OneDrive\Documents\GitHub\Mechanize_takehome\client\src\components\CanvasPage.tsx#L573): initial HTTP bootstrap can overwrite newer websocket state, so a connected client can regress to an older board snapshot.
- `[P2]` [ws.py](C:\Users\sahil\OneDrive\Documents\GitHub\Mechanize_takehome\server\app\ws.py#L202): malformed websocket `canvasId` values are still not rejected cleanly before the UUID-backed membership query runs.

**Notes**

The actual session-5 wiring in [main.py](C:\Users\sahil\OneDrive\Documents\GitHub\Mechanize_takehome\server\app\main.py#L40) looks correct: routers are mounted and the websocket route is registered. The integration pass did happen. The remaining failures are cross-boundary behavioral bugs, not missing glue.

